{"Q0":"It was a little repetitive. Maybe the longer tasks could be broken into maybe 1 more section, just to give a break, because I think people who do the whole thing are committed and want to do their best and give good and accurate data.

Also, maybe explain that you CAN select 0 or 100 if you want or it feels appropriate. At first I thought you meant for us NOT to select those, but I figured it out. Just a little unclear at first.

One last point: are you expecting any specific minimum number of remembered words to be typed out, or just a time spent on that part? I thik respondents might feel insecure that they are not doing enough without any guidance there."}

{"Q0":"First of all, thank you so much for having me. I didn't really have a strategy going in. Everything was just how I felt or how i've been feeling and just answer based on that. 

but that was a great study and it actually made me reflect on myself and how i'm doing mentally

Thank you again"}

{"Q0":"I didn't employ any strategies, I just tried to take an honest look at myself and accurately rate each word. I don't feel great but then again, I never do...so that's nothing new. I can't think of any ways to improve the task.

I don't know if it's relevant but I've been depressed for close to but not quite 25 years, severely depressed for close to 20 years. I've received no help for it, my family either doesn't notice or don't care, and have just suffered alone the whole time. No therapy, no meds, no friends to talk to, no family to really talk to.Just me alone.

Thank you very much for the opportunity to assist with your research."}
